  "title": "Accounts & Admin Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will manage full sets of accounts and perform month-end closing for small entities. You will organize finance documents, monitor payment matters, and process petty cash and staff claims. You will also handle administrative tasks and work in a motorcycle workshop environment.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Apply comprehensive knowledge of full sets of accounts to maintain accurate financial records</li><li>Perform month-end closing activities for small entities to ensure timely financial reporting</li><li>File and organize finance documents to maintain easy access and compliance</li><li>Check payment statuses and follow up with relevant parties to resolve outstanding issues</li><li>Process petty cash transactions and staff claims accurately and promptly</li><li>Complete administrative ad hoc assignments as required to support finance and workshop operations</li><li>Work safely and effectively within a motorcycle workshop environment</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Achieve GCE 'O' Level or Diploma qualification with preferably at least 2 years of accounting experience</li><li>Demonstrate proficiency in English to communicate effectively in the workplace</li><li>Exhibit computer literacy to perform accounting and administrative tasks efficiently</li></ul>",
